BLOEMFONTEIN - The African National Congress (ANC)’s Free State elective conference finally got underway in Bloemfontein on Saturday. The conference, meant to start on Saturday morning, suffered a five-hour delay as registration of delegates took longer than anticipated. It eventually began at around 3pm. READ: Free State ANC fuming over Manuel's Magashule comments About 400 delegates are attending the conference, which is being overseen by at least eight members of the ANC's National Executive Committee. Some members claimed due process was not followed in preparing for the conference. eNCA